    <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin:6px 0 6px;">🏷️ Seller Platform</h3>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--soft);line-height:1.55;">Standalone seller web + mobile app. Owners submit their business → your team verifies it through review checkpoints → approved listings publish <b>live</b> into the main buyer marketplace via the shared Supabase backend (a data change, no redeploy). Build the <b>submission flow + verification console in P1–P2</b> so real listings flow in; the polished <b>seller mobile app is a fast-follow</b>. Full detail on the Seller Platform page.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="reality">
    <b>Solo-founder reality check:</b> shipping <i>both</i> verticals + mobile + payments + eSign + escrow in 26 weeks alone is very aggressive. To de-risk: (1) lean hard on AI for code + content, (2) ship each vertical to an internal milestone before polishing, (3) buy don't build for compliance — engage a <b>CA/company-secretary</b> for incorporation/GST and a <b>vendor</b> for eSign/escrow rather than custom work, (4) consider one <b>contract React Native dev</b> for the Nov mobile push, and (5) keep a 2-week buffer before Dec 19 for bug bash. If timelines slip, the cut line is: launch SMB marketplace fully + Corporate M&amp;A in beta.
  </div>

